    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>LABEL OWNER SUES MP3.COM</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Laurie J. Flynn</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Flynn, Laurie J</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Zomba Recording files lawsuit against MP3.com, accusing it of willful copyright infringement in relation to its MyMP3.com site; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Zomba Recording said it had filed a lawsuit against MP3.com, the online music distributor that only last week was found in violation of copyright law in a similar suit filed by the Universal Music Group. The lawsuit accuses MP3.com of willful copyright infringement in relation to its MyMP3.com site, a service that lets users listen to the company's CD collection over the Internet. Zomba's Jive label records some of the biggest pop acts today, including Britney Spears, above, the Backstreet Boys and 'N Sync. A sister company, Zomba Music Publishing, filed a separate suit on the same ground.</p>
        <p>Laurie J. Flynn</p>
      </block>
